1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Susan
2 Maureen Brothers Mayo.
3 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo was born on February 6, 1948, in
4 Maysville, Kentucky to proud parents, Maurice and Wilma Brothers; and
5 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo was a proud Maysvillian and dedicated
6 alumna of the Maysville High School Bulldogs Class of 1966, known as the "Slicks of
7 '66"; and
8 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo attended Eastern Kentucky University
9 and dedicated her career to hospitality, bringing kindness and friendship to everyone she
10 met. Whether she was managing hotels throughout Kentucky and South Carolina or
11 serving as Maysville's Tourism Director, she served her community and shared her love
12 for her hometown with people throughout the country; and
13 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo's presence in the radio broadcast
14 industry at WFTM made her a familiar and comforting voice in Maysville, allowing her
15 to connect with people throughout the community; and
16 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo's unwavering commitment to her
17 community and her love for her family have left an indelible mark on all who knew her;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo departed this earthly life on May 25,
20 2024, leaving behind a legacy cherished by her family, friends, and the entire community
21 of Maysville; and
22 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo was preceded in death by her beloved
23 parents, Wilma Perry and Maurice "Buddy" Brothers, and her brothers, Robert "Bob"
24 Brothers and James "Jimmy" Brothers, all of whom provided the foundation of love and
25 dedication that she carried forward in her own life; and
26 WHEREAS, Susan Maureen Brothers Mayo was a shining example of
27 unconditional love as a single mother, and she is survived by her two loving sons, Kelly
